IT Technician

Company Summary
Holler Law Firm, LLC is a family-oriented and employee-led business with a successful multi-state real estate closing practice. We provide a unique solution to the title insurance industry by leveraging cutting-edge technology, innovative business solutions, and a growth-oriented operational model. With nearly two decades of experience, Holler Law Firm provides exceptional real estate closing services to our dedicated portfolio of clients, who have trusted us with their business for many years. Our dynamic environment offers unique career opportunities for driven individuals to meet new challenges and grow within the organization.

Position Description
Holler Law Firm is looking for an IT Technician to join our Information Technology team. The ideal candidate would have 2+ years of experience in the Information Technology field. The position is open to candidates who are detail oriented, organized and can demonstrate the ability to work quickly, accurately and under pressure with minimal oversight. Candidates must be capable of multi-tasking while maintaining precise attention to details. This is a full-time, non-exempt, 40-hour, hybrid position with 2-3 days per week in the Milford, CT office. This position reports to the IT Manager.

Responsibilities Include (but not limited to):
Receiving and processing help desk requests for employees, clients, and vendors;
Identifying issues that need expert support and escalate to internal or external resources;
Supporting and maintaining hardware, software and network equipment as necessary;
Managing IT assets and inventory;
Managing new hire setups, including shipping and configuration of equipment, and technical training;
Acting as point of contact for outside IT, and other experts;
Participating in IT projects through testing, communication, implementation, and training;
Provisioning and deprovisioning of user accounts in internal and third-party systems;
Identifying opportunities to improve, automate, or simplify processes or systems;
Other administrative tasks and projects as assigned.
What You Need:
Minimum 2 years of experience in IT, preferably in a help desk or desktop support environment;
Working knowledge of common hardware and popular operating systems;
Ability to effectively communicate with employees about technology who have a wide range of technical skills, both in-person and remotely;
Genuine eagerness to train and learn about new technology and systems;
Platinum level Customer Service Skills;
A willingness to embrace our unique and wonderful culture of commitment and open communication.
Nice To Have:
Certifications such as A+, Network+, Cloud+ ;
Windows Server 2019;
Microsoft 365, with a focus on collaboration features;
Experience with Intune or similar MDM;
Experience with Citrix;


Full, Affordable Benefits
Health, Dental, Paid Time Off, Paid Holidays, Retirement Savings Plan with Employer Match, Flexible Spending Account (FSA), Employee Assistance Program, Employee Discount Program, and more! Waiting periods apply.

